<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="528" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d528">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.4016 <gloss target="#t_DP1">DP</gloss>/7–545: Airgram</note>
                                <head>No. 528<lb/><hi rend="italic">The Assistant to the President’s
                                        Personal Representative at Vatican City</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_THH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Tittmann</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#left">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                                    </seg>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vatican City</hi></placeName>,
                                            <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-05">July 5,
                                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>
                                    <gloss target="#t_A1">A</gloss>–17. Referring to my Airgram 12
                                    of June 29, 1945,<note n="1" xml:id="d528fn1">Not
                                        printed.</note> the following is translation of Note
                                    received from Holy See dated July 5, 1945:<note n="2" xml:id="d528fn2">A similar communication of May 22 with
                                        respect to Lithuanians in Germany and <persName corresp="#p_I2">Italy</persName>, and Latvians and
                                        Estonians in Germany, was transmitted to the Acting
                                        Secretary of State by <persName corresp="#p_TMC1">Myron C.
                                            Taylor</persName>, the Personal Representative of the
                                        President at Vatican City, in telegram No. 118 of May 22
                                        (file No. 800.4016 <gloss target="#t_DP1">D.
                                        P.</gloss>/5–2245).</note>
                                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                                        <p>“Several thousand Ukrainians are in Germany and fear that
                                            they may be sent to Galicia.</p>
                                        <p>“On their behalf the Holy See has been requested to use
                                            its good offices in order that these poor refugees may
                                            soon be allowed to leave Germany and to take refuge in
                                            France, Belgium, the Netherlands, or any other country
                                            rather than being obliged to go to territories under
                                            Russian domination.”</p>
                                    </quote>
                                </p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <persName corresp="#p_THH1">
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tittmann</hi>
                                        </persName>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>